Method behavioural requirements:
- The integer parameter `n` represents the number of integers in the array `arr`.
- The integer parameter `m` represents the maximum value of each integer in the array `arr`.
- The integer parameter `k` represents the value of `search_cost` after applying the algorithm to the array `arr`.
- The integer result is the number of ways to build the array `arr` under the mentioned conditions, computed modulo 10^9 + 7.